title.narrative: COMMUNICATION FOR DEVELOPMENT (C4D)

description.narrative: By 2021, COs and partners are equipped with Communication for Development (C4D) quality standards, region-specific guidance and partnerships for improved management, coordination and leadership of community engagement, behavior, and social change programming at scale in development and humanitarian contexts with emphasis on the most deprived children., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Immunization. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: RO and COs implement adequate cross sectoral strategies to improve programming excellence and achieve quality and equitable results for children.

description.narrative: In addition to substantial support and leadership for Covid-19 RCCE response in WCAR, with special attention to vaccination, social listening and community feedback, WCARO C4D contribution to regional KRCs increasingly focused on inspiring and equipping the regional C4D network to gain agility for enabling sustainable social and behavior change. This happened through innovative promotion of concrete human rights-based approaches beyond traditional communication that enact service providers and policy makers’ accountabilities, and through faster research, measurement and documentation. This set solid ground for the organizational shift from Communication for Development to "Social and Behavior Change," that officially starts in January 2022. | Status:Met | As-of Date:08/03/2022
